Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The property has been a James Island Public Service District fire station since 1961.  It is 1.012 acres with 210 feet of frontage on Camp Road just off Folly Road.  There are two building on the site.  The front building is a brick building of 5,013 SF built in 1961 which could be a retail or office/flex use and and the back building is a metal building of 4,500 SF built in 1984 for a total building area of 9,513 SF.  There is plenty of parking and additional laydown/parking potential onsite.  The property is in the Town of James Island and is zoned OG.  Landlord is willing to subdivide to fit tenants needs.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: Retail or Flex Office for Lease

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
5,611 Square Feet available at Stono Station. Stono Station was renovated in 2019 and 2020 including new landscaping, exteriors, blade signage. Last remaining spaces available.  

Space is a former restaurant and owners would consider future uses to include restaurant, office, or flex.  Outdoor seating may be accommodated for end-cap restaurant use.
